[11] Pakistan (Sindh)
Date: Tue 13 May 2014
Source: Samaa TV [edited]
http://www.samaa.tv/health/13-May-2014/chief-justice-shc-takes-suo-motu-of-measles-outbreak


Chief Justice (CJ) of the Sindh High Court (SHC) has taken suo motu notice of over a dozen measles-related deaths of children in Sujawal and Thatta districts of Sindh, SAMAA reported [Suo motu, meaning "on its own motion," is a Latin legal term approximately equivalent to the term sua sponte. For example, it is used where a government agency acts on its own. - Mod.CP].

The CJ issued notices to the Secretary of Health, Chief Secretary and officials of Thatta district administration to appear in the court on Wednesday [14 May 2014] and file their responses over the matter.

Officials said over 12 children have died so far in measles outbreaks in Sujawal and Thatta, with hundreds of measles cases reported in villages of the 2 worst-hit districts.

