[13] Philippines
Date: Sat 17 May 2014
Source: Minda News [edited]
http://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2014/05/17/160-measles-cases-recorded-in-surigao-city/


City health workers have conducted a massive vaccination drive here against measles as cases continue to rise, officials said.

Annette Villaces, city information officer, said that 160 persons, mostly children, have been afflicted by the viral disease from 1 Jan to 13 May this year [2014]. City health officials declared a measles outbreak on 3 May 2014.

The massive vaccination drive is continuing in the different villages [districts] in the city to combat the disease, targeting children 6 months to 4 years old. Dr. Romulo Ybiernas, chief epidemiologist of the Surigao City Health Office, said the vaccination drive includes mostly the villages of Taft, Washington and San Juan, where most of the victims reside.

The Department of Health in Region 13 (Caraga Region) has dispatched personnel from the Regional Epidemiology and Surveillance Unit to help combat the disease, Villaces said.

[Byline: Roel N. Catoto]

